    revision: 
  upmReserved: '{"changelog":"### Added\n- Added UI Toolkit world-space support to
    `XRRayInteractor` for Unity 6.2.0 and newer, enabling ray-based interaction with
    UI Toolkit panels in XR environments.\n- Added z-depth poke support for world
    space UI Toolkit Buttons and Toggles.\n- Added a Manager Singleton Mode to the
    XR Interaction Toolkit project settings to automatically destroy additional XR
    Interaction Manager components in order to keep only a single active and enabled
    manager across all loaded scenes to avoid issues with interaction components
    being registered with multiple, different managers unintentionally and preventing
    interaction between them. The default project setting continues to allow multiple
